# UI Mockup Conventions

When creating or editing any page, screen, or widget, follow the App Template
mockup. Reference: `.cursor/rules/assets/mockup.png`.

## Design Language
- Minimal, clean, modern. Generous white space, light neutral backgrounds.
- Card-based layouts: white cards, large rounded corners (~16px), soft subtle
  shadows. No hard borders.
- Rounded inputs and buttons. Primary buttons are full-width, filled, rounded.
- Use Google Fonts for typography; clear hierarchy (bold titles, muted subtitles).

## Theming
- Drive all colors from a single theme via `ThemeData` / `ColorScheme`. Never
  hardcode colors in widgets.
- Support an easily swappable accent color. Reference palette: blue (default),
  red, orange/yellow, green, purple, teal.
- Status/stat icons use colored circular backgrounds matching the accent set.

## Structure & Navigation
- Bottom navigation with 5 sections: Home, Tasks, Calendar, Messages, Profile.
- A floating action button (`+`) for primary creation actions.
- Standard screens to mirror: Splash, Login/Register (email + Google/Apple),
  Home (greeting banner, Overview stat cards, Recent Activity list), Profile
  (avatar, stats row, action list), Settings (grouped sections with chevrons).

## Components
- Build small, reusable, responsive widgets (organized layers). Extract cards,
  list items, and stat tiles into shared widgets instead of duplicating.
- List rows: leading icon, title, optional trailing value/chevron.
- Keep spacing and padding consistent across screens.
